 In celebration of spring

 Doordarshan Kendra, Calcutta presents Vasant Utsav featuring classical music, light vocal music and classical dance. The festival will be inaugurated this afternoon at 4 by the Union minister for information and broadcasting and parliamentary affairs, Priya Ranjan Das Munshi. The inaugural days programme features classical instrumental and vocal music by renowned artistes. Participants: Shivkumar Sharma (santoor), Ganesh and Kumaresh (duet violin), Vishwa Mohan Bhatt and Ronu Majumdar (mohan veena and flute duet), Ali Ahmed Hussain (shehnai), and vocals by Rashid Khan, Ulhas Kashalkar and Prabhati Mukhopadhyay. Among those who will perform tomorrow (9 pm onwards) are Ajoy Chakraborty, Shubha Mudgal (vocals) and Lavanya Anant (Bharata Natyam). Participants on March 4 include Dr Balamuralikrishna, Girija Devi and Parveen Sultana (vocals). The concluding days performance features Haimanti Shukla, Nirmala Misra, Usha Uthup, Raghab Chattopadhyay, Partha Ghosh, Gouri Ghosh, Soumitra Chattopadhyay and others.

